Invocation Name: computer science wiki
des: This skill lets Alexa provide you with definitions for common concepts and syntax that used in the programming world. All you have to do is tell Alexa to "open computer science wiki", and then ask away. You can say "Alexa, what is the definition of a while loop?" or "Alexa, what is an interface?", and she will give you a concise, helpful explanation of the word. This can be helpful while studying if you forget what a specific piece of syntax means, or if you just want to brush up on your fundamentals before heading to an interview.
priv: The developer reported that this skill does not collect personal information.
